-- Australian Dollar Declines as Growth Slows, Central Bank to Hold Key Rate
-- Garfield Reynolds
-- 2010-07-04T23:26:49Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-04/australian-dollar-declines-as-growth-slows-central-bank-to-hold-key-rate.html

          
          
             The Australian dollar fell toward a
three-week low on expectations the central bank will keep
interest rates unchanged tomorrow for a second month amid signs
the global economic recovery is slowing. New Zealand’s currency
also weakened.  
 The so-called Aussie declined to 83.83 U.S. cents as of
9:24 a.m. in Sydney from 84.16 cents on July 2 in New York. New
Zealand’s dollar slid 0.4 percent to 68.56 U.S. cents.  
